Defendant Lucas R Lindner in court with attorney David Allan Nelson.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 2, 3 and 4 are dismissed and read in.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

8 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 0 days )
- 3 Years of Initial Confinement
- 5 Years of Extended Supervision

Term of Probation: 3 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
-No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
-Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
-Inform agent of all prescriptions;
-Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Doctor's identity to be released to agent so the Doctor's can be informed of this case;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- No contact with James and Ashley H .
- Do not possess any dangerous weapons as set forth in 939.22(10); 
-Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge. 

Costs: $268.00 BAIL TO APPLY
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00 BAIL TO APPLY
(Remaining to be paid as a condition of probation within the first 6 months.)   

Condition Time: 6 months Huber NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS -  Last 90 days Stayed to be used at the agent's discretion.  

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.
